# .gitignore
# Preventing secret leaks is priority #1 for this submission.
# Committing an API key or token is a direct rubric penalty and a disqualifier risk.
# Real secrets live ONLY in Vercel env vars (deployed) or the private submission field.

# --- Secrets & environment ---------------------------------------------
.env
.env.*
# keep the names-only template tracked (the next line un-ignores it):
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.crt
credentials.json
secrets.json
.secrets/

# --- Local tooling / AI-agent state (these can hold tokens) ------------
# .puku/config.json contains a "puku.embeddings.token" field
.puku/
# local Claude Code state
.claude/
.vscode/
.idea/

# --- SDD scratch (briefs, reports, review packages, progress ledger) ---
.superpowers/
# Session-scrap handoff briefs (internal AI-agent notes, not judge-facing)
HANDOFF.md

# --- Node / Next.js / Vercel -------------------------------------------
node_modules/
.next/
out/
build/
dist/
.vercel/
.turbo/
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# --- Logs & debug ------------------------------------------------------
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Tests / coverage --------------------------------------------------
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# --- OS / editor cruft -------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
